\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Could I ask you your name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 My name is Jack Brenner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 And your address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 My - my address now is - 9 Mocatta House, Brady Street, London, E1.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 What year were you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 I was married in 1929.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 And your year of birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 1900.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 I was born Bathson Street. And that turning is not there today. That is off of Valance Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Do you know how many years you lived in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Well - I remember - waking up I was in the pram, and I was four years of age. And I started crying.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 You remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 And that was in the house in Buckson Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Yes. In Buckson Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Do you know how many years you lived there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 I believe - I must have been about - I believe about five years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Do you know where you went after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Yes, I went to - Eric Street, Mile End Road, near Burdett Road.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Is that the house you remember most as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Yes, yes. And from there - I went to Princes Square. And lived there - of course - until I got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Do you know why your family moved, why they made these moves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Well - I mean everybody tr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13587160\charrsid209760 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13587160\charrsid209760 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760  to get better accommodation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 You think that's why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh yes, I'm certain of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 How many brothers and sisters were there in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Including myself there were four - well three brothers and four sisters, and myself was four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 What was their birth order, how many years in between roughly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Well I - I - I've still go a younger sister. She's about - I should say about sixty - I say about sixty-eight. I've got a b
rother he's eighteen months younger than myself. I had a brother, he died - he died - about 1966. I've got a sister - she's about eighty-three, and - I've got another sister, she's seventy - five. Who's in Australia. And I had another sister older than my
self, she would have been about seventy-three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 So there was quite a bit of difference in between you wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh yes, yes, yes. Oh yes, quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 You had one younger than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 No, I had a sister younger than myself. She's in Canada. And I had a brother younger than my - younger than myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Do you know where your father came from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 He came from - Lithuania.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 How old was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 He died when - he died at seventy-two. And my mother also died at seventy-two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Do you know how old your father was when you were born?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 That I wouldn't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Would he be a young man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 I know he was in the Russian Army.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Did he come over here as a young man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 I - as I - oh definitely, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 And he met your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 No, I believe he met her in - Lithuania, 'cos she came from the same - well, a different town you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 What was your father's occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 He was a small master-builder. He employed men, and - besides doing - they say, roof work - houses that want - wanted re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13587160\charrsid209760 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 
pointing - he also did - oven work. He used to climb in the hot ovens you see because they never - put them out you see. And he used to put in what they called a kay-kay tile - tile, that was like a reddish ti - tile, you know, fo
r mending the - in the ovens. Oh he was a very strong man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Was he apprenticed when he was over in Lithuania?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 That I wouldn't know. That I wouldn't know. No, no, no. Because - if you remember - at the time fathers were very strict. Any little thi
ng - over the chair with a strap. You couldn't ask 'em too many questions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Was that the only job you think he had here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh definitely. Oh yes, well - you see, besides that there was about twenty - houses in the street. He worked for an agent you
 see, and they had quite a lot of property. Well in the street they had about twenty or thirty houses, and he used to collect the rents - every Monday morning. Oh he was well known in the street, 'cos I mean - we lived there quite a - quite a number of ye
ars.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 And he'd employ some men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh yes, definitely, yes, yes. Mm. Yes, he had}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13587160\charrsid209760  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 one of them - one of them small handcarts, a builders truck rather, you see. And of coursed I mean they were these - because they had a - like a shaft you see, and they'
re quite easy to pull along you see, they was on two wheels.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Do you think that would have been quite a good business at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh yes, oh - oh yes, yes, yes, because wages were very small them days. The average wage, 'cos I - wasn't my fath
er earned I don't know, but the average work - wage for working man was about thirty shillings a week. But of course the - the foodstuffs and everything was much cheaper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Do you ever remember your father being out of work, or having difficult periods when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 That I wouldn't know. I wouldn't know, no, I wouldn't know that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 He didn't ever do any part time jobs of any sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh no, no, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 He was always a master builder?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh yes, yes, always that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 What about your mother, you said she came from Lithuania as well, did she ever have a job when you were a child, did she ever work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Women didn't work them days. No. Very seldom. Unless - unless, we'll say, in the clerical profession, see, young - young g
irls used to go to work you see, but as soon as they - as soon as they - got married, well - then they didn't work any longer. It's different than is today. When I start - I started work I star - started work in a grocery shop - at two and six a week. Eig
h
t in the morning 'til eight o'clock at night. And every Friday I had to scrub a floor - the floor of the shop out. I had the Saturday and Sunday off. I stopped there - fifteen months, and all I had was - the wages were increased up to seven and sixpence. 
A
nd because I asked for a rise I - I had to find another job. Oh definitely. 'Cos the next job I was working for Everley Heaps the hatters. Used to have a shop in Corn Hill, you know, near the bank. And - I started off with twelve and sixpence a week there
. But I don't think I got - many - any more increases.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 What did you do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 
Well more or less they used to get a lot of - hat - hats - you see - this was a very exclusive hat shop. And - people like the - manager of the Bank of England, the Lord
 Mayor of London, very well known people would buy their hats there. Well they used to take off the old hats and leave 'em behind, and that, so I mean there's quite a lot of straw hats. Well it was my job to clean these hats. Also cleaning the windows and
 
- and also cleaning the floor you see once a week. And going out for odd errands, see, but - also - there used to be people - they used to leave their hat every day, every night, these bank managers, silk top hats, and it was a free service, the hats woul
d be ironed and I had to take these hats round to these bank managers - bank - messengers rather.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 They'd leave them in the evening would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 That's right, leave them in the evening and - in the morning -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 On their way home from work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 
No, not - not from work, they'd leave 'em, see a bank messenger - they used to wear these silk hats, top hats, and - when they were finished, like go - towards going home way, they would leave 'em in the shop, you see, because otherwise they must have wor
n say a bowler, because at the time there was all either silk hats or else bowler hats. Well today you hardly see anybody walking about with hats at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 How long did you stay in the house that you moved to when you were about five years old? The hous
e off Mile End Road. Do you think you spent most of your childhood there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh no, no, no, no. No. I was there about three years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Can I ask you about the house you went to after that, what road was that in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Can you stop - stop a minute? Say from about 1908 until - until 19 - 29. When I got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 That would be the one you'd remember most?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Yes, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 How many rooms were there in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Well - in the house there was - let me see - there was a - one - one - 
downstairs downstairs was one, two rooms. Two rooms on the - landing, that's four. Six eight, ten rooms. Ten rooms in the house. And if anybody - took the whole house they could have had it for a pound a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 How much of the house did your family have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 But actually - actually we have - the basement and the ground floor. That was - four rooms.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 How would they be divided up, what would the rooms consist of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh - there was a bedroom in the front room, a large - we called it eating room, 
or a kitchen if you like. A very large dresser, with two drawers and a very large old fashioned fireplace. The fireplaces at the time - they had to be blacked over, you understand, because they used to use a black - black polish. Black polish - and a brus
h
, and they used to clean 'em up and they used to come up like a pair of shoes, see, and there was also a oven, but near - with the fireplace, a very tall fireplace, say about - say about five foot high. Then there was a - we'll say a dining room on the gr
ound floor, and another bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Two bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 And a dining room and a kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 
Yes, yes, and - and we also had a bath - a bath - a bathroom, because my father never used it. You see, because - perhaps he wanted some - re
pairing, but he - very often used to keep quite a lot of his tools in there, and paints and various other things you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 It actually had a bath in it did it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 That's right, oh yes, it did have a bath, and - then there was a big yard that we - made into a ga}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13587160\charrsid209760 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 
den. There was also a glass house, but of course the glass wanted repairing, and there was the - a vine with grapes, that was still growing. Because I suppose once upon a time this must have been a very - well - to - do street, and that is th
e reason why they have - the Prince of Sweden buried in the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 That's where you say the Swedish church was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh yes, yes, yes, yes. There were - and - 'course they used to have - big oak trees there, in the - in the church - grounds. A
nd - 'course later - later - the - Prince - the body of the Prince was taken back to Sweden. And there used to be a German - band playing there every Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Was he an exile over here or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 No I don't think so, I don't think so. I - we
ll I - I don't know - actually the history, but - I could have found out. I could have found out perhaps from the - libraries, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Would a lot of Swedes come to use the church?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 That I - I don't know. No. I mean I remember when the church 
was in full swing and - when they used to have a vicar there and there used to be - a big house in the corner where he lived. And of course quite - well dressed people - would come there, but who they were, I mean, I was only a child, I wasn't interested 
in that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Did anyone beside}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13587160\charrsid209760 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4859080\charrsid209760  your parents and brothers and sisters live with you in your house, any lodgers or any relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 No, no relat - no lodgers, I mean, my brothers and sisters lived there, until they got married. And once they go
t married well - they become less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Did your mother ever have anyone to help in the house? Did she ever pay anybody to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh no, no. Well - them days - speaking about laundries, doing the washing - there was no - there were one or two - like -
 shops where they washed collars and shirts, you understand, but once - once a week my mother - she would do the washing, it would take her all day long. You see, the houses used to have - iron boilers, what they called coppers, and there was like a fire 
underneath, you know, put in coke, and - you used to - and of course they - they enjoyed doing it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 You were talking about your mother doing the washing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh yes, yes, well - well I think I - I did tell you - she used to do this washing of - of a W
ednesday, and it - it was an all day job. That's all I can say about that. And she enjoyed doing it. Oh definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Did your mother or father make or mend any of the family clothes? Do you remember your mother making clothes or mending them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh yes, yes, yes. Oh yes, my mother would mend - mend - mend the clothes, yes, quite definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 You don't know if she'd make clothes for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 No, she didn't make.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 You'd buy clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh yes, yes, certainly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Do you know where she'd buy your clothes, the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13587160\charrsid209760 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 s clothes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 
Well, either in the Lane, Petticoat Lane, or else - in the - not in the same street but the first turning left, that's Cable Street. There was a shop there, they used to sell - clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 That's where you can remember your mother going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Mm. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Did you always have new clothes or did you ever have second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13587160\charrsid209760  }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 hand clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh no, no, always new clothes. Always new clothed definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Did you have them for any special occasions, new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 No, not particular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 When you needed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Just - yes, just when they were needed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 What about shoes, would your father repair your boots -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh yes, yes, that - that he could do, yes, yes, he had a last, and - he'd - he - he used to mend our shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Where would you buy shoes or boots from? Somewhere locally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Do you know how much boots or shoes cost in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 I don't remember. I was too young to know. But - there's one things I can 
tell you, 'course it may be on your question - regarding - coal or coke - most people used to buy coke, and coke used to cost one pound - for one ton. You know the price of it today. Ay? A ton. Twenty hundred weights.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 How much is it now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Well, c
oal is - I believe coal is about eighteen pound a ton. That's a big difference isn't it? Also - regarding lighting. Most of the houses have - had at the time, I'm speaking about - between - let's say about 1908, as far as I can remember you understand - e
ither - paraffin - lamps - or else - of course there was gas, gas fixed you see but they used to use the inverted - and the upright mantles. And all the street lamps all had gas. With in - with - invertible gas or - upright mantles.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 What was your house lit by?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 
It was lit by - for an emergency we had the - the lamp - the lamp, paraffin lamp, but it was lit by gas, with either inverted or - or the upright mantles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Did your father ever help your mother with any of the jobs in the house, can you remember ever him doing anything like cleaning or cooking?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 No. No, no, no, no. Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 What about lighting fires? Would he ever light the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh yes, mother used to light the fires.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Not your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Would your father ever do any decorating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 
Oh yes, yes, oh definitely. Oh of course - well - certainly, he - he - he'd always - he'd always - he'd paint - paint inside the rooms or paper hanging. Ceiling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Did he ever help with the children at all, your father, would he ever dress you or undress you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 
Oh yes. Oh yes, yes. I can remember - he liked to - always liked to get up at six o'clock in the morning, his regular habit at six o'clock in the morning, getting up. Many times he - I can remember him carr
ying me, you know, form the ground floor - down to the - down to the - basemen}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13587160\charrsid209760 t, call it the basement see, we}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 
ll say a dozen steps go down, and making tea and I mean - and he always loved a strong cup of tea. But he - he - he liked plenty of water. He used to drink plenty of water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Would he bath the children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 No, we used to go to the baths. Yes, the public baths.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Would he ever read to you or tell you stories, your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Well, that was the trouble, he couldn't read English. Understand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Would he ever tell you stories about Lithuania, would he ever talk to his children about it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 No, no, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Do you think that was because he had been unhappy there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 That - no, I - that I don't know. That I don't know. I 
never - I'd never question him on anything like that. We had a cellar where we used to keep this coke. I wonder - once went down there without permission. He says to me, never do that again. You understand? Strict. So - if you go - if you go and ask your 
parents - about certain things, what happened in - country where they come from - you - you would know all about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 And even your mother didn't talk much about where she'd come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh no, no, no, she was very - she was very good - at making pastries. She was an expert - expert cook, expert pastry maker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Would your father ever look after you, after the children if your mother wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh yes, definitely. Oh sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Did you have any tasks you had to carry out at home regularly when you were a little boy, any jobs about the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 
Only - only going for errands. I mean - I think every - everybody - everybody - I mean if - if we were told to go and - get something, we would get it without any arguments.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 You didn't have to help your mother in the house at all with anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh no, no, no. We were - no, we were actually too young you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 As you grew up you didn't have special jobs to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh no, well I left school at fourteen, you see. And I'm still a youngster, and then I was - then I was small for my age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 What about your sisters, would they have to help your mother at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh yes, of course they did. Oh yes. Amusements at the time I'm speaking about, this is say between the 1900's going on - wer
e actually the only type of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13587160\charrsid209760 amusement}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 
 was either - dance halls - cinemas, in their early beginnings, and we as children paid a penny - to go to the cinema, and some cinemas we paid a ha'penny. Now I went to a cinema once - and we children, they put us at t
he back of the screen, so the words were - double }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13587160\charrsid209760 ditch}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 
, because we couldn't understand the words, you understand. All you could see was just the pictures of the silent altogether - there was also - we used to play cards. Now and again there were - like wh
at you call evenings in - evenings in, fellows - fellows and girls would like - put so much together, in fact very often we had quite a lot in the house where I - where I lived. All right? And - they would have games, forfeits - youngsters kissing, you kn
ow what I mean - playing the piano and singing, and spend a happy evening. I don't know if there's anything else I can -
\par 
