\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 You said you had a couple of part time jobs when you were at school to earn a bit of money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 What about your first full time job, after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 My 
first ful time job I started - at two and six a week in a grocery shop. Eight in the morning 'til eight o'clock at night, five days a week. Friday - night I used to - I had to scrub the - the shop floor, see this is in the grocery shop. I stopped there fi
fteen months, and I asked for a rise and - the highest wages I had was at the time was - was seven and sixpence. And I - I wouldn't - couldn't get a rise so I left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 What was the employer like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh he was a strict man but he wasn't bad on the whole
, but - it was a job where - where you had to earn - you had to earn this money, although it was small - hundredweight bags of flour I had to weigh up in pound and two pound bags, sugar the same thing, lump sugar - used to come in hundred weight - cases, 
used to use a scoop, and when you - and when the scoop wasn't handy you had to used your hands. And you could tell what your hands were like, lump sugar, weighing 'em up, used to make your hands all rough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Did you get any paid holidays in that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 No, no, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 What did you go on to next?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 
I had the job in a hat - a man's hat shop, in the City. Henry Higgs, they were hatters to the King. They had a branch in Moorgate Street, they had a branch in - Oxford Street. At the finish they went bankrupt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 What did you have to do?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 
Well - at one - at one period - I would - you see - at this firm Henry Higgs - only the - only the - the - people who knew the job thoroughly were serving in the shop you see. My job was - clean the floo
r on a Friday night. People used to come in and buy hats, customers, you see they had good customers, they also had an index - say, if a person they used to measure - his - measure his head you see, then they used to put it like say on a file, now the old
 
hat although it was clean and good, they were all put in one side. He never wore that hat - that hat again you know. They were sold to Dunn's. Now the straw hats had to be cleaned, so we used to clean these hats, we'd clean these hats up. And of course th
e
re was quite a lot of - other things that we used to do. I always - I always used to go round to the factory. See they had - beside having a - a branch - in Oxford Street, they also had a factory, see round the back, and I used to go upstairs on the first
 floor and - block out some of the shapes. See, they'd show you how to do it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 How much were you paid at that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Twelve and six a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 So that was a rise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 That was a rise, see, yes, yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Did you get any holidays there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 What was the employer like, was it one man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh no, no, no, no. Only a - only a - a manager.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Was there any trade union activity there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 No. I don't think so. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Where did you go on after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Well I had - I had a few m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1914757\charrsid209760 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 n - minor jobs, you understand, a few weeks here and a few weeks there until I joined the army. Mm. Mm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 And when you came out of the army is that when you started street trading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 That was after 1918?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 
Mm. Yes. Although I actually started before - actually started before - when I - when I used to work in this first shop, in this grocery shop - I walked in one day and - one day - in Petticoat Lane, a cousin of mine - we - we go through a street c
alled - what's the name of the street, I - well we were going through this street, I just can't remember the name - looking in the shop window, we were called in the shop. Have you got any money? Said, oh yes, we've got sixpence each. Well, that's plenty 
o
f money. He says, buy a half a dozen of these - treasure note wallets, it's a cardboard thing, you turned it inside out you know, I don't know, you might have seen it. He says, sell 'em for sixpence each. And took us - half a day to sell 'em. We sold 'em 
at sixpence each. See? The six cost us a shilling you see, we sold 'em for - one and sixpence. Oh no, we sold 'em for three shillings, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Two shillings profit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Yes. And of course we carried on every week like that you know what I mean 
until - my cousin - had enough of it and I - was the governor myself and 'course from one line went to another line you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Would you keep this money yourself or would you give any of it to your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh no, but - can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Do you think you'd have hung on to it to invest it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 No, I don't - no, no, no, no. I mean - my wages - my wages - I used to have sixpence pocket money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 In the grocery shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 In the grocery shop. When I joined the army - what did I have, I think I had seven and sixpence and my parents had the rest. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 What about your home life after you left school, did you go on living at home once you left school and started your first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh yes, I lived at home until I got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Did starting work change your relationship with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Or with your brother and sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 No, no, no, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Did they treat you any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 What about Sundays or Saturdays, did you spend them any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 I don't think so. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Did you go on going to any religious service at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 I did until - until I got married. I was orthodox when my - while my parents were alive, you understand. After that I more or l
ess forgot about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Were you interested in politics at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Not ever, not even now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 What about your spare time when you were a young man, once you'd left school, did you do anything different with your time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Did you ever go out in the evenings? Were there places around here you could go out and enjoy yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Well we'd go into - go to the park, Victoria Park that time or - go to the - cinemas, the early cinema}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1914757\charrsid209760 s. Or go for long walk}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 s.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Did you make any new friends in any of your jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh yes, oh - oh yes, yes, sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Did your parents allow you to take friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 They were quite happy to welcome them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 In the street where I l
ived there was a Salvation Army. And - there used to be men - men - like - like - sleeping there, lodging there you know, and the - the - Captain - Captain Butler at the time, his son, oh we used to be great friends. I used to go into - his home and he us
ed to come into my home. Even when I joined the army, he came round on a visit - with his father to my place. And 'course he was disappointed not seeing me 'cos I was in the army, but of course he left his regard you know. Oh we were great friends.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Wo
uld boys go out with girls then, how old were people before they began to have girlfriends, obviously today it's very early, would you say it was later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Well - I remember - a girl got married at sixteen - and it was the - it was the gossip of the street, if you understand what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 She was so young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Did your parents expect to know where you were once you were a young man and you'd left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh no. Oh no. Oh no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Did you have to be home at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Not particular, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 
Can you remember anything you'd have to eat when you were a boy, any meals, can you remember what you'd have for lunch or any special meals your mother cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 I can't remember, I know - I know we didn't starve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Did you eat quite a lot of meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh yes. Oh yes. Yes, yes. Plenty of meat and plenty of fish. Plenty of food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 So you would think you ate well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh definitely, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Would you have a cooked meal when you came in from school in the evening or would you have a cooked meal at lunchtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 That - that is. 'Course I can say Saturday and Sunday we always had a cooked meal. But - during the week I can't - can't say off hand.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 You had one brother, what did he do for a living, did he do anything different from you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 
My brother was - a supervisor - in various firms. He was - his last job was - he was working with - some very big firm of - chemists. Although he retired - at - I imagine about two years ago, he's working for Singers
, the swe - sewing machine people, and - he had a job in the office as a organizer, by all accounts he was doing quite well. Only of course I haven't seen him lately.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 What about your sister? Did she work at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Oh yes, my sister, she worked for Rachel Tucks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 That's something to do with cards isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Or stationary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 That's right. That place in - in Moor - Moorgate Street, near Lon - near London Wall
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10036353 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Was that an office job of some sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8133147 JB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4859080\charrsid209760 Secretary.
\par }}